{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"712052ac-4feb-4cbf-b2a9-63d0d6f3840f","content":"Use MAUI's `#if` preprocessor directives or the `OnPlatform` pattern in `MauiProgram.cs`:\n\n```csharp\n// MauiProgram.cs\npublic static MauiApp CreateMauiApp()\n{\n    var builder = MauiApp.CreateBuilder();\n    builder.UseMauiApp<App>();\n\n#if ANDROID\n    builder.Services.AddSingleton<INotificationService, Platforms.Android.AndroidNotificationService>();\n#elif IOS\n    builder.Services.AddSingleton<INotificationService, Platforms.iOS.IosNotificationService>();\n#elif WINDOWS\n    builder.Services.AddSingleton<INotificationService, Platforms.Windows.WindowsNotificationService>();\n#endif\n\n    return builder.Build();\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- Place each implementation under its `Platforms/<OS>/` folder so it only compiles for that target.\n- The `#if` symbols (`ANDROID`, `IOS`, `WINDOWS`) are defined automatically by the MAUI SDK per target framework.\n- Only one branch compiles per platform, so missing platform APIs won't cause build errors.\n- Inject `INotificationService` via constructor injection anywhere in shared code — the right implementation resolves at runtime.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4403bba0-bcde-4093-9b29-1f140836f505","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI dependency injection — specifically how to register platform-specific implementations of an `INotificationService` interface in `MauiProgram.cs`. This is a general knowledge question, not a codebase-specific task.","outputTokens":378,"requestId":"102E:2A621F:150A9E4:17B6217:69FD3630"},"id":"449b11a9-18ea-4b37-adfa-91f4b20951e8","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:02:49.337Z","parentId":"2fe885a3-690f-45d9-bd7f-4a49640a2712"}
